      "html": "<h4> Patterns Represented by Quadratics</h4>\n<p>See Steps 1&ndash;3 of a pattern of squares below. Write an equation representing the relationship between the step number \\(n\\) and the number of squares \\(y\\).</p>\n<p><img alt height=\"213\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/4ccf3dd0ae2703ffe11b06fc46c1a04927a29997\" width=\"300\"></p>\n<p>Make a table for the number of columns and rows of each step and the number of squares:</p>\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n  <colgroup>\n    <col width=\"91\">\n    <col width=\"78\">\n    <col width=\"80\">\n    <col width=\"80\">\n  </colgroup>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p><strong>Step</strong></p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p><strong># of columns</strong></p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p><strong># of rows</strong></p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p><strong># of squares</strong></p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>1</p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>1</p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>3</p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>3</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>2</p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>2</p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>6</p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>12</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>3</p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>3</p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>9</p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>27</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>\\(n\\)</p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>\\(n\\)</p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>\\(3n\\)</p>\n      </td>\n      <td align=\"center\">\n        <p>\\(3n^2\\)</p>\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n<br>\n<p>First, count how many columns there are in each step (the length):</p>\n<p>For each, there are \\(n\\) columns.</p>\n<p>Next, count how many rows there are in each step (the height):&nbsp;</p>\n<p>For each, there are \\(3n\\) rows.</p>\n<p>The area of this figure is then \\(l \\times h\\) or \\(n \\times 3n\\), which becomes \\(y=3n^2\\).</p>\n<h4>Try It: Patterns Represented by Quadratics</h4>\n<p>See Steps 1&ndash;3 of a pattern of squares below. Write an equation representing the relationship between the step number \\(n\\) and the number of squares \\(y\\).</p>\n<br>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta\" data-button-text=\"Solution\" data-fire-event=\"Reveal1\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\">\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-content\">\n    <p><img alt height=\"90\" role=\"presentation\" src=\"https://k12.openstax.org/contents/raise/resources/7459295e7469e7c1d9d58452ad23659f223e851f\" width=\"304\"></p>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"os-raise-ib-cta-prompt\">\n    <p>Write down your answer, then select the <strong>solution</strong> button to compare your work. </p>\n  </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"os-raise-ib-content\" data-schema-version=\"1.0\" data-wait-for-event=\"Reveal1\">\n  <p>Here is how to represent this pattern as a quadratic:</p>\n  <p>Make a table for the number of columns and rows of each step and the number of squares:</p>\n  <table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"5\">\n    <colgroup>\n      <col width=\"91\">\n      <col width=\"78\">\n      <col width=\"80\">\n      <col width=\"80\">\n    </colgroup>\n    <tbody>\n      <tr>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p><strong>Step</strong></p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p><strong># of columns</strong></p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p><strong># of rows</strong></p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p><strong># of squares</strong></p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>1</p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>0</p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>0</p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>0</p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>2</p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>2</p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>2</p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>3</p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>3</p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>3</p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>3</p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>8</p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n      <tr>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>\\(n\\)</p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>\\(n\\)</p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>\\(n\\)</p>\n        </td>\n        <td align=\"center\">\n          <p>\\(n^2-1\\)</p>\n        </td>\n      </tr>\n    </tbody>\n  </table>\n  <br>\n  <p>For this pattern, notice that the area would be the number of columns times the number of rows, but then one block is subtracted.</p>\n  <p>Note that for Step 1, there was a \\(1 \\times 1\\) block there, but then it was subtracted with the equation given.</p>\n  <p>The equation, then, is \\(y=n^2-1\\).</p>\n</div>"
